High-level Goal: Identifying high-risk patients for diabetic retinopathy and eye disease using metabolic indicators.

📝 Project Overview
This project analyzes a dataset of 20,000 patients to correlate metabolic factors (glucose, cholesterol, obesity) with eye health outcomes. It features a custom Health Risk Scoring system to prioritize patient care based on clinical severity.

🛠️ Technical Stack
Core Libraries: Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib.

Feature Engineering: Calculated metabolic_risk_count and health_risk_score from raw physiological data.

Categorical Analysis: Segmented patients by BMI (Obese, Overweight, Normal, Underweight) and Blood Pressure categories.

🚀 Key Implementations
Risk Stratification: Built logic to flag "Metabolic Syndrome" based on cumulative risk factors including sugar levels and systolic/diastolic pressure.

Clinical Insights: Discovered that Obese patients represent the largest segment (7,978 records), highlighting a critical demographic for preventative eye care screenings.

Automated Flagging: Converted boolean health indicators into binary integers for seamless integration into machine learning training pipelines.
